# QA REPORT: Activity Status

## Requirement 1 — Activity Status Tracking
**Status**: PASS

**Code Location**: 
- Backend: [f:\COD_CHECK\UI_MANAGER\backend\core\workflow\bot_orchestrator.py](file:///f:/COD_CHECK/UI_MANAGER/backend/core/workflow/bot_orchestrator.py) ([BotOrchestrator](file:///f:/COD_CHECK/UI_MANAGER/backend/core/workflow/bot_orchestrator.py#15-439) logic)
- Frontend: [f:\COD_CHECK\UI_MANAGER\frontend\js\pages\workflow.js](file:///f:/COD_CHECK/UI_MANAGER/frontend/js/pages/workflow.js) ([_updateActivityStatuses](file:///f:/COD_CHECK/UI_MANAGER/frontend/js/pages/workflow.js#1207-1271) function)

**Implementation Explanation**:
- Backend [BotOrchestrator](file:///f:/COD_CHECK/UI_MANAGER/backend/core/workflow/bot_orchestrator.py#15-439) uses a dictionary `self.activity_statuses`. It tracks each activity's state: "pending", "running", "done", "error", or "skipped".
- The state changes naturally as the executor loops through `self.activities`. Before executing an activity, it marks it as "running". Upon success, it sets it to "done". On exception or timeout, it sets it to "error".
- Frontend listens to `bot_queue_update` over WebSocket padding it into the UI with the `acv-status-{id}` badge.

**Execution Path Check**: 
The code is executed within the main [_execute_current_account](file:///f:/COD_CHECK/UI_MANAGER/backend/core/workflow/bot_orchestrator.py#103-111) loop of [BotOrchestrator](file:///f:/COD_CHECK/UI_MANAGER/backend/core/workflow/bot_orchestrator.py#15-439), successfully reaching all conditions. (Runs sequentially).

**Issues**: 
- **Minor Terminology Difference**: The backend uses "done" instead of `COMPLETED`, and "error" instead of `FAILED`. The frontend translates these to "Done", "Error", "Queued", "Running", "Skipped". It logically matches the SPEC CHECKLIST but differs slightly in literal string outputs (SPEC mentioned `PENDING, RUNNING, COMPLETED, FAILED, N/A`).

