## Requirement 3 — UI Status Indicator
**Status**: PASS

**Code Location**: 
- Frontend: [f:\COD_CHECK\UI_MANAGER\frontend\js\pages\workflow.js](file:///f:/COD_CHECK/UI_MANAGER/frontend/js/pages/workflow.js) ([_updateActivityStatuses](file:///f:/COD_CHECK/UI_MANAGER/frontend/js/pages/workflow.js#1207-1271))

**Implementation Explanation**:
- The UI filters [getActivityConfig()](file:///f:/COD_CHECK/UI_MANAGER/frontend/js/pages/workflow.js#829-844) for enabled activities and updates their badges by id (`acv-status-${id}`).
- Maps: `pending` -> Queued, `running` -> Running, `done` -> Done, `error` -> Error, `skipped` -> Skipped.
- Overrides status string to "Stopping" if `queueData.stop_requested` is true and status was "running".
- If a user hasn't checked a feature (disabled), it skips updating that activity's status badge (leaving it to its default "N/A").

**Execution Path Check**:
Function is triggered every time `bot_queue_update` is received from the server.

**Issues**:
None found.

